  "title": "The System Lied",
  "subtitle": "The System told me my class was Paladin. I was a Necromancer. By the time I figured it out, I had eleven corpses in my shed.",
  "penName": "Blake Thornton",
  "genre": "litrpgSystem",
  "hook": "The System awakened me on a Tuesday in November and assigned me Class: Paladin. I spent three weeks failing to heal anyone. On the fourth day I raised a dead squirrel from the sidewalk and the System said OH RIGHT, THE PALADIN THING. YEAH. ABOUT THAT. My real class was Necromancer. The System was petty. Buffalo was overrun. I had eleven corpses in my shed by Friday.",
